{"type": "article", "id": 22994, "title": "日本人设计一本《东京客》，连字体都和纽约那个一样", "description": "是非常认真的致敬呢。", "date": "2016-02-29T13:10:07Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 1384, "name": "纽约客"}, {"id": 24121, "name": "东京客"}, {"id": 24122, "name": "封面插图"}, {"id": 14406, "name": "独立杂志"}, {"id": 11844, "name": "恶搞"}], "category": 17, "author": 37534, "comment_count": 2, "praise_count": 153, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160702101153mIdoXfx0j4srgAlV.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p>无论是<a href=\"http://www.newyorker.com\">《纽约客》（The New Yorker）</a>还是<a href=\"http://theparisianer.fr/en/\">《巴黎人》（The Parisianer）</a>，这两本以城市名称命名的杂志都有着鲜明的插画风格。最近，两位东京设计师也凑起了热闹——他们发起了一个叫《东京客》（<a href=\"http://www.spoon-tamago.com/2016/02/26/the-tokyoiter-imaginary-magazine-covers-inspired-by-the-new-yorker/\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The Tokyoiter）的封面设计项目，</a>邀请当地艺术家仿照《纽约客》的风格设计封面，结果连字体都和《纽约客》一样啊。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101149XrIROEPHaDjVGiMq.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.56333333\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\">这就是那本《东京客》了，杂志封面充满了当地色彩</figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101149xUlrATngGdY04wOm.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.33428571\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">日本拉面出现在了《东京客》的封面上</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021011502OjPL6komvWdSHcZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.33428571\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">第二个封面也和“吃”有关</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101150vxoIA9hFq5QXt4fO.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.33428571\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\">东京街道，fancy 咯</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>这两个玩儿心大发的人是艺术家 Andrew Joyce 和 David Robert，他们邀请了当地艺术家为杂志画封面，主题就是“尽可能地展现东京的美和特点”。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101151XHzITtMNn5AjK6Or.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.46\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">图片下标注的是画家的名字</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>在<a href=\"http://www.thetokyoiter.com/about/\">杂志的官方网站</a>上，他们这样写道，“东京这座神奇的城市，随时充满了故事和灵感。我们希望通过封面设计的项目展现东京的迷人之处。也借此机会，向《纽约客》杂志表达敬意。”</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101151tZJrpefHlzCaPvcy.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.41365462\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">《东京客》</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p class=\"\">再来回顾一下《纽约客》和《巴黎人》的插画风格吧：</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101152tIjZQPn9xYlLSs7D.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.54787234\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">《巴黎人》</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101152NAE64iaj1wxhyR3M.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.54787234\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">《巴黎人》</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\">\n<figure class=\"placeholder\"></figure><figure class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101153wjDhFSQimGJAsU2n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.443\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">《纽约客》杂志过往封面</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702101153n9k8SXtr3uFKUdYv.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.54787234\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">《巴黎人》杂志过往封面</div></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n<p>题图来源：<a href=\"http://www.spoon-tamago.com\">spoon-tamago</a></p>\n\n"}